<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-21T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-21T10:00:00-05:00" n="132" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d132">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/1144: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Acting Chairman of the American Delegation (<persName corresp="#p_GHS1" type="to">Gibson</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-21T11:00:00-04:00">June
                                        21, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>142. Your 265, June 21, 1 p.m. The President and I are greatly
                                relieved. We approve your suggestion to postpone presentation until
                                Wednesday afternoon and shall arrange for simultaneous publication
                                of statement here in Washington. Further details as to arrangements
                                will be cabled to you.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>